Keter-class items don't have to be specifically hostile toward humans. They don't even have to be sapient. There really isn't a strict set of criteria, but in my time here I've seen that they generally should fail the locked box test and have very significant consequences (not necessarily ) They can also be poorly understood, making it difficult to be certain whether it is being fully contained. But that's just my understanding. Others may interpret it differently.







